AngloGold, ArcelorMittal, Nu-World May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-05-10T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/anglogold-arcelormittal-nu-world-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 475.78, or 1.5
percent, to 32,085.56 at the 5 p.m. close of trading in
Johannesburg, its highest since May 3.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  : The world’s third-biggest
gold producer releases first-quarter earnings. AngloGold gained
3 rand, or 1 percent, to 311 rand.  ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. (ACL)  : The local unit of
the world’s biggest steelmaker releases first-quarter earnings.
The company’s stock jumped 1.10 rand, or 1.4 percent, to 82.10
rand.  Chrometco Ltd. (CMO)  : The ferrochrome development and
exploration company said it revalued its Rooderand chrome
mineral assets and its attributable monetary value is
“substantially lower” than for its inferred resources.
Chrometco was unchanged at 33 cents.  Gold Reef Resorts Ltd. (GDF)  : The South African hotel
and gaming company said it expects earnings per share for the
twelve months through March 2011 to be 28 percent to 33 percent
lower than for the previous period. Gold Reef slipped 48 cents,
or 2.8 percent, to 16.52 rand.  Nu-World Holdings Ltd. (NWL)  : The South African
manufacturer and distributor of domestic electric appliances
said earnings per share fell 9.7 percent to 152.4 cents in the
first half through February, according to a regulatory filing.
Nu-World fell 1 rand, or 4.4 percent, to 22 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Franz Wild  in Johannesburg at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at   barden@bloomberg.net . 